snippet.textDisplay: As funny and goofy as this was I as a musician found a lot of help in this video. Often when you go to school for music and you study and study and study, you find yourself losing track of simplicity. I can write counterpoint in 17th century european style easily now but pop songs I struggle with. It's almost like I overthink everything when im trying to write. I think too hard about trying to create some masterpiece rather than writing what I'm feeling or thinking. My brain tells me that it needs to be more complicated and like everything I need to write needs to be some genius composition. But it's a lot simpler than that. You lose emotion with thoughts like that and trying to force emotion into a complex piece turns into the feeling of trying to hold water in your cupped hands. It eventually falls apart. I may try my hand at song writing again. Thank you for this video.
